                                       boolean convertTo8bits,
                                       boolean maximizeValuesRange,
                                       MetaDataRetriever.RetrievalPolicy retrievalPolicy)
                                throws java.io.IOException
        Constructs an instance by loading the image from a source file.
        Parameters:
        path - path to the image source file on disk.
        convertTo8bits - If true, the image created is converted to color type GRAY8 to save resources.
        maximizeValuesRange - If true, values are scaled linearly so as to set their maximum to (2getBitDepth()-1).
        retrievalPolicy - The policy to retrieve predefined metadata for the resource of type ImageCore.
        Returns:
        Instance of the Image as built by a constructor of the actual wrapper.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - IOException in case of failure to load the image from file
        See Also:
        MetaDataRetriever.RetrievalPolicy

      • getEmptyImageCore

        public abstract ImageCore getEmptyImageCore(int width,
                                            int height,
                                            int depth,
                                            int bitDepth)
        Allocates and returns a black image with given dimensions and type (GRAY8 or GRAY16). The gray levels are uninitialized, the image has a default title and no meatdata such as calibration data.
        Parameters:
        width - Width of the image in the first voxel coordinate
        height - Height of the image in the second voxel coordinate
        depth - Depth of the image in the third voxel coordinate
        bitDepth - Number of bits per voxel
        Returns:
        An instance of ImageCore implementer
        See Also:
        ImageCore.getImageCalibration(), ModelCoreGeneric.addMetaData(wrapScienceJ.metaData.container.MetaDataRetriever)

      • createFromRegularArray

        public abstract ImageCore createFromRegularArray(short[][] voxelValues,
                                                 int width,
                                                 int bitDepth)
        Converts an array of voxel values to an ImageCore. The size of the array, which is an array of 2D image values, must be the same as (or larger than) the size of the image which generated this instance. The memory from voxelValues is recycled into the new image if bitDepth is 16. Otherwise, bitDepth must be 8, the memory from voxelValues is left unchanged and a new byte image is allocated.
        Parameters:
        voxelValues - A 3D array containing the values of the image.
        width - Width of each slice of the image to create (the height is obtained through width and voxelValues[0].length, which must exist and be multiple of width.
        bitDepth - The number of bits per voxel of the new image (values are truncated in case of overflow).
        Returns:
        The image as an ImageCore implementer's instance.

      • createFromRegularArray

        public abstract ImageCore createFromRegularArray(byte[][] voxelValues,
                                                 int width,
                                                 int bitDepth)
        Converts an array of voxel values to an ImageCore. The size of the array, which is an array of 2D image values, must be the same as (or larger than) the size of the image which generated this instance. The memory from voxelValues is recycled into the new image if bitDepth is 8. Otherwise, bitDepth must be 16, the memory from voxelValues is left unchanged and their values are copied (embedded) as is into a newly created image.
        Parameters:
        voxelValues - A 3D array containing the values of the image.
        width - Width of each slice of the image to create (the height is obtained through width and voxelValues[0].length, which must exist and be multiple of width.
        bitDepth - The number of bits per voxel of the new image (values are truncated in case of overflow).
        Returns:
        The image as an ImageCore implementer's instance.
